<?xml version="1.0"?>
<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5">
  <title>graphite_pickle</title>
  <para>The graphite module provides a simple way to push data into reconnoiter via the carbon-relay pickle format.  Simply configure the relay to write to the provided port.</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>loader</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>C</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>image</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>graphite.so</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <section>
    <title>Check Configuration</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>listen_port</term>
        <listitem>
          <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>required</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>optional</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>default</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>2004</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>allowed</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>[0-9]+</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
          <para>Specify the port which this check listens on.  Carbon relay or carbon-c-relay should be configured to send plain text metrics to this port.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>rows_per_cycle</term>
        <listitem>
          <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>required</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>optional</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>default</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>100</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>allowed</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>[0-9]+</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
          <para>The max number of rows to process in one event loop.  Defaults to 100.  Turn this up higher if you have very high volume metric collection.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <example>
      <title>Ingesting graphite data</title>
      <para>
        <code>
          [example]
           pattern = ^mydata\.foo\..+
           servers = broker:2003
        </code>
      </para>
      <para>The carbon relay config example above will direct any metrics starting "mydata.foo" at the broker:2003 for ingestion</para>
      <programlisting>
      &lt;noit&gt;
        &lt;modules&gt;
          &lt;module image="graphite" name="graphite_pickle"/&gt;
        &lt;/modules&gt;
        &lt;checks&gt;
          &lt;check uuid="1b4e28ba-2fa1-11d2-893f-e9b761bde3fb" module="graphite_pickle"
            target="127.0.0.1" period="60000" timeout="30000"&gt;
            &lt;config&gt;&lt;listen_port&gt;2004&lt;/listen_port&gt;&lt;/config&gt;
          &lt;/check&gt;
        &lt;/checks&gt;
      &lt;/noit&gt;
      </programlisting>
    </example>
  </section>
</section>
